author: cnbc.com
title: TriNet: 1Q Earnings Snapshot
text:
SAN LEANDRO, Calif. (AP) _ TriNet Group Inc. (TNET) on Monday reported first-quarter earnings of $54 million.
The San Leandro, California-based company said it had net income of 75 cents per share. Earnings, adjusted for one-time gains and costs, were 80 cents per share.
The results topped Wall Street expectations. The average estimate of five analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for earnings of 63 cents per share.
The human resources services outsourcing company posted revenue of $861 million in the period. Its adjusted revenue was $220 million, also exceeding Street forecasts. Four analysts surveyed by Zacks expected $216.3 million.
TriNet shares have increased 16 percent since the beginning of the year. In the final minutes of trading on Monday, shares hit $51.65, a climb of 76 percent in the last 12 months.
